##Wuhan outside: Many villages and towns lack isolation measures, epidemic prevention propaganda, county-level hospitals shortage of materials

Micro-signal. NBWEEKLY

Introduction of function, new media with temperature

The following article is from Southern Metropolis Daily, author of the Southern Metropolis Daily

NANDU, do it another way

On the 25th, the city of Wuhan was sealed off for the third day. According to incomplete statistics, at least 18 cities (counties) in Hubei have taken access control, restrictions on urban traffic and other city closure measures.

The rate of confirmation of COVID-19 infection has increased rapidly, with the number of new cases in the last four days jumping from 149 to 444. The cumulative number of cases has exceeded 1,000, rising from 440 on the 21st to 1,287 on the 23rd. As of press time, the number of confirmed cases was further increasing.

In Wuhan, the focus of the epidemic, many citizens have told Nandu, have tried to wear masks, home disinfection and other protective measures, has also cancelled family gatherings.

However, the self-protection consciousness and epidemic prevention measures in the surrounding cities and rural areas of Wuhan are not optimistic.

On January 25, the official account of the People's Daily also said that the situation of prevention and control of NCP is serious, but the prevention and control of NCP in rural areas need urgent attention. The article said that many people returned home during the Spring Festival, the level of medical care in rural areas is limited, and the awareness of prevention and control among farmers is relatively weak. According to this, the People's Daily initiative to keep track of the movement of Personnel, do a good job of screening and registration, to avoid gathering crowds, to do a good job of door publicity and inspection.

Although some areas have taken measures to prevent the epidemic, but many residents outside Wuhan to the south are said that the surrounding residents wear masks proportion is not high. Some villages and towns have not recently returned from Wuhan and other places to take any registration, temperature testing, tracking, and even isolation and other measures.

In addition, Wuhan's designated hospitals are already suffering from shortages, overcrowding and shortages in the surrounding county hospitals, which have even weaker facilities. Lack of protective clothing, lack of goggles, lack of gloves, gap masks... almost every hospital is making such a sound.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Catch the last bus before Wuhan shuts down

At 2 am on the 23rd, Wuhan announced that it would close the city at 10 am on the same day, and that the airport and railway stations would be temporarily closed from the Han corridor. He's brother-in-law took the last bus from Wuhan to his hometown of Suizhou.

Since then, more than a dozen counties and cities in Hubei Province have begun to adopt traffic control measures.

He said it was "very sudden" that the notice of the closure came out of Wuhan, and that his aunt almost took a black car in order to get back to Suizhou before the closure, only to be dissuaded by her family.

It wasn't until the city closed in Wuhan that he realized the seriousness of the situation. "before the closing notice came out, many people thought it was exaggerated to wear a mask. "

Just on the 21st, she said, she was in her hometown in Suizhou and saw a lot of medical masks lying quietly in the pharmacy, no one patronized. As soon as news of the closure of the city of Wuhan broke on the 23rd, Suizhou's masks, alcohol and disinfectant were quickly snapped up.

He Xian's home from Wuhan by car more than two hours, many friends and neighbors from Wuhan rushed home for the New Year. People returning home from the field struggle to explain how dire the situation is, but their families are skeptical.

"For example, my uncle's family, cousins seem to have no such awareness. " Envy Helpless Way.

He said he saw no other public health measures, other than the suspension of public transportation. She bought disinfectant and alcohol from out of town, and her family disinfects them when they come home.

The office of Suizhou's COVID-19 pneumonia command issued an information circular on the 24th, reporting that as of 2400 hours on the 23rd, 493 patients with fever had been admitted to Suizhou, bringing the cumulative total of suspected cases of COVID-19 pneumonia to 42, there were 15 new cases.

The implementation of grid management and household search, registration

On the 22nd, the COVID-19 was set up to coordinate the organization of special classes. At a meeting of the prevention and Control Headquarters on the 24th, Jiang Chaoliang, secretary of the CPC Hubei Provincial Committee and Commander of the provincial new type of pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters, proposed to implement grid management, house-to-house investigation, registration and other prevention and control measures, do a good job of quarantine observation and treatment of relevant personnel, and strengthen policy publicity, guide the masses to rest at home, do a good job of self-protection.

In Hubei provinces and cities, prevention and Control Command institutions have also been set up and designated medical institutions have been set up. Yingshan County and Xuan'en County are under the unified command of their respective pneumonia prevention and control headquarters.

For example, on January 22, the Chongyang County County Government in Xianning organized the implementation of the "Chongyang County COVID-19 pneumonia prevention and control work program" , request that the situation of returning people be checked out as soon as possible and report to the township government the list of returning people, their mobile phone number, time of returning to Chongyang County, list of people in close contact, etc. . The key personnel of each township organization are required to go to the village-level clinic to have their body temperature measured once a day for at least two weeks. In addition, the village of small stores, supermarkets, early stalls, vegetable stalls, January 24 at 6:30 pm to the eighth day of the Lunar New Year closed, and the village to engage in Dragon Lantern, dragon boat activities.

Measures to prevent epidemics in villages and towns are limited, and residents want to step up publicity

On Jan. 22, the day before Wuhan's closure, 51.5 percent of the population moving into Xiaogan came from Wuhan, according to data monitored by Baidu's eyes on maps-baidu migration. In addition to Xiaogan, Huanggang, Ezhou, Xiantao, Xianning, Suizhou, Huangshi and other places, also had more than 20% of people from Wuhan direction moved in that day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At the same time, residents of several villages and towns in Wuhan have said to the south that local measures to deal with the epidemic are extremely limited.

Mr. Wang returned home from Wuhan a few days ago to celebrate the New Year. Not many people wear masks through the villages. "about two out of ten people" . With the spread of the epidemic and the disclosure of information, according to his observation, the proportion of people around the mask has an upward trend, but also only reached the "only 10 in 4,5" level.

Although people around him are talking about the epidemic, in his view, the awareness of prevention has not kept up. He told Nandu, most of the neighbors will take disinfection measures at home, but most are using vinegar or common disinfectant, less scientific, less professional.

According to the COVID-19, published by Wuhan Tongji Hospital of Huazhong University of Science and Technology, based on studies of SARS coronavirus and Mers coronavirus, the coronavirus is heat sensitive and remains at 56 °C for 30 minutes, ethyl ether, 75% ethanol, chlorinated disinfectants, Peracetic acid and chloroform are effective in inactivating the virus. Chlorhexidine is not effective in inactivating the virus.

Xiao Wu, who lives in a village in Ensch, Hubei Province, recently returned from Wuhan. "I have not received any publicity, investigation or registration for ten days since I came home, " she told Nandu, there is only a small amount of information.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"The countryside is really a propaganda blind area, especially in rural Hubei Province. It's really a place where there are a lot of people returning home from Wuhan. ". According to her, some residents who returned home from Wuhan on the 23rd of the 12th month were still attending parties and had not taken measures to isolate themselves.

Residents of a town in the city of Dazhi, Huangshi, also told Nandu that there had been little local publicity for the outbreak, "which everyone knows from watching the news on TV. ".

The good news is that some areas have taken action in good time. For example, Zhijiang on the 22nd issued a "letter to the city's residents, " in which, the virus harm, personal protection measures.

A local resident also told Nandu that Zhijiang would also register people returning from Wuhan.

Hospitals around Wuhan are in short supply of protective materials

On the evening of January 24, and the New Year's Eve of New Year's greetings together with the screen of friends circle, there is such a message: "Wuhan Urgent Help! "

The article introduces: Wuhan Many Hospitals Material is tight, may only be able to maintain 3-5 days, at present the hospital requests the urgent support. Hospitals Including Union Medical College Hospital, Tongji Hospital and other designated treatment hospitals for patients with fever in Wuhan have asked for donations of protective materials such as goggles, face masks and protective clothing urgently needed by medical staff.

The News of material shortage was reprinted by many media. Wuhan a Three-a hospital doctors also told Nandu before, because colleagues infected him to go to the top shift, but there is no protective clothing, can only find their own, buy.

In fact, not only Wuhan lack of materials, and Wuhan together with the other cities sealed off the city, but also in a material shortage situation. On the 24th, the Xiaogan Center for Disease Control and Prevention issued a public notice to open a channel for charity donations to receive protective materials. Hospitals in Hanchuan, Jingzhou and elsewhere have also announced their acceptance of donations.

What about the hospitals in Wuhan's outlying counties, already starved of supplies, overcrowded and even less well-equipped?

On January 22, the official website of Xiaogan First People's Hospital released a press release entitled "Safety Ward Round, with emphasis on the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia. " The photos showed the medical staff participating in ward rounds wearing white coats, wearing a surgical mask while examining the critical area. It said the inspection team "urged medical staff to wear hats, masks, eye masks and protective clothing to strengthen their own protection. ".

A doctor at a hospital in Yichang, Hubei, told Nandu that the hospital currently has no emergency protective clothing, can only wear disposable operating clothes, and must be used repeatedly, goggles, masks and other materials are also in short supply.

"We're giving out one mask a day, and we're basically three days away from no masks, " he said.

It is noteworthy that in addition to protective materials, virus detection kits are also in short supply. Takatomi, a member of the Expert Group of the National Health Commission, said in an interview on the evening of March 23 that patients admitted to the hospital could not be tested for pathogens in time, leading to cross infection.

After the closure of the city, Internet users around the city have forwarded the news of the shortage of medical supplies. Also has the netizen spontaneously to establish the material docking group, hoped that helps the hospital, the patient seeks the manufacturer, the Logistics Company and so on.

Some of the residents interviewed in Nandu had taken measures to isolate themselves from their families, while others had asked them to stay at home as much as possible. But he Xian said, the elderly at home still want to go out, he can only strongly dissuade, do disinfection.
